[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":1119},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Freact\u002F2022\u002F09\u002F16\u002Freact-day-02-hello-react\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Freact\u002F2022\u002F09\u002F16\u002Freact-day-02-hello-react\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Freact\u002F2022\u002F09\u002F16\u002Freact-day-02-hello-react\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Freact\u002F2022\u002F09\u002F16\u002Freact-day-02-hello-react\u002F":1096,"related:\u002Fen\u002Freact\u002F2022\u002F09\u002F16\u002Freact-day-02-hello-react\u002F":1105},"\u002Freact\u002F20220916\u002F2624842138\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":1077,"date":1078,"description":1079,"extension":1080,"lang":1081,"meta":1082,"navigation":553,"path":1083,"readingMinutes":1084,"seo":1085,"standalone":1086,"stem":1087,"tags":1088,"tldr":1093,"updated":1078,"url":1094,"__hash__":1095},"content\u002Fen\u002FReact\u002Freact-day-02-hello-react.md","You'll Learn React Eventually, So Why Not Now? — React Basics: Hello React (2)","1002969628",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":1067},"minimark",[11,16,20,24,27,67,70,73,85,88,95,99,102,168,171,218,233,236,245,256,265,298,301,305,313,316,342,345,356,391,397,413,446,449,466,505,511,578,588,593,596,642,647,650,661,671,675,682,778,783,789,793,799,915,920,923,1014,1018,1027,1031,1034,1040,1047,1051,1054,1063],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"intro","Intro",[17,18,19],"p",{},"Earlier we took a quick look at the syntax differences between React and Vue, so now it's time to actually start getting to know and learning React.",[12,21,23],{"id":22},"a-heads-up-before-we-start","A Heads-Up Before We Start",[17,25,26],{},"Since we're going to be learning React Hooks soon, and React kind of expects you to have a decent grip on the JavaScript basics, here are the bits of syntax I'd really recommend you pick up first:",[28,29,30,34,37,40,43,46],"ul",{},[31,32,33],"li",{},"Arrow functions",[31,35,36],{},"The spread operator",[31,38,39],{},"The rest operator",[31,41,42],{},"Object destructuring",[31,44,45],{},"Array destructuring",[31,47,48,49],{},"Array methods\n",[28,50,51,57,62],{},[31,52,53],{},[54,55,56],"code",{},"map",[31,58,59],{},[54,60,61],{},"filter",[31,63,64],{},[54,65,66],{},"forEach",[17,68,69],{},"Now, it's not that Vue never uses these. It's just that if you're a complete beginner who's never touched Vue, the ones above are the ones I'd strongly suggest getting comfortable with.",[17,71,72],{},"On top of that, if you want to go deeper on JavaScript, you might also want to check out a blog series I wrote before:",[28,74,75],{},[31,76,77,84],{},[78,79,83],"a",{"href":80,"rel":81},"https:\u002F\u002Fisraynotarray.com\u002Fjavascript\u002F20200307\u002F318160061\u002F",[82],"nofollow","JavaScript Core Concepts"," (article in Mandarin)",[17,86,87],{},"Hopefully this little plug helps you learn JavaScript happily.",[17,89,90],{},[91,92],"img",{"alt":93,"src":94},"As long as everyone gets to be happy, that's all that matters","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FJavaScript\u002F%E4%BE%86%E8%87%AA%20Vue%20%E7%9A%84%20React%20Hook%20%E9%96%8B%E7%99%BC%E8%80%85\u002F1653200556906.png",[12,96,98],{"id":97},"react-cdn","React CDN",[17,100,101],{},"For our practice here, we're going to use React's CDN. I've already written out the CDN for React 18 below, so take a look at these URLs:",[103,104,109],"pre",{"className":105,"code":106,"language":107,"meta":108,"style":108},"language-html shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","\u003Cscript crossorigin src=\"https:\u002F\u002Funpkg.com\u002Freact@18\u002Fumd\u002Freact.development.js\">\u003C\u002Fscript>\n\u003Cscript crossorigin src=\"https:\u002F\u002Funpkg.com\u002Freact-dom@18\u002Fumd\u002Freact-dom.development.js\">\u003C\u002Fscript>\n","html","",[54,110,111,146],{"__ignoreMap":108},[112,113,116,120,124,128,131,134,138,141,143],"span",{"class":114,"line":115},"line",1,[112,117,119],{"class":118},"sMAXC","\u003C",[112,121,123],{"class":122},"sKpQp","script",[112,125,127],{"class":126},"sCcAr"," crossorigin",[112,129,130],{"class":126}," src",[112,132,133],{"class":118},"=",[112,135,137],{"class":136},"sTRMh","\"https:\u002F\u002Funpkg.com\u002Freact@18\u002Fumd\u002Freact.development.js\"",[112,139,140],{"class":118},">\u003C\u002F",[112,142,123],{"class":122},[112,144,145],{"class":118},">\n",[112,147,149,151,153,155,157,159,162,164,166],{"class":114,"line":148},2,[112,150,119],{"class":118},[112,152,123],{"class":122},[112,154,127],{"class":126},[112,156,130],{"class":126},[112,158,133],{"class":118},[112,160,161],{"class":136},"\"https:\u002F\u002Funpkg.com\u002Freact-dom@18\u002Fumd\u002Freact-dom.development.js\"",[112,163,140],{"class":118},[112,165,123],{"class":122},[112,167,145],{"class":118},[17,169,170],{},"One thing to note here: the React CDN we're using for practice is the development build. If you'd rather use the minified version, you can switch to this instead:",[103,172,174],{"className":105,"code":173,"language":107,"meta":108,"style":108},"\u003Cscript crossorigin src=\"https:\u002F\u002Funpkg.com\u002Freact@18\u002Fumd\u002Freact.production.min.js\">\u003C\u002Fscript>\n\u003Cscript crossorigin src=\"https:\u002F\u002Funpkg.com\u002Freact-dom@18\u002Fumd\u002Freact-dom.production.min.js\">\u003C\u002Fscript>\n",[54,175,176,197],{"__ignoreMap":108},[112,177,178,180,182,184,186,188,191,193,195],{"class":114,"line":115},[112,179,119],{"class":118},[112,181,123],{"class":122},[112,183,127],{"class":126},[112,185,130],{"class":126},[112,187,133],{"class":118},[112,189,190],{"class":136},"\"https:\u002F\u002Funpkg.com\u002Freact@18\u002Fumd\u002Freact.production.min.js\"",[112,192,140],{"class":118},[112,194,123],{"class":122},[112,196,145],{"class":118},[112,198,199,201,203,205,207,209,212,214,216],{"class":114,"line":148},[112,200,119],{"class":118},[112,202,123],{"class":122},[112,204,127],{"class":126},[112,206,130],{"class":126},[112,208,133],{"class":118},[112,210,211],{"class":136},"\"https:\u002F\u002Funpkg.com\u002Freact-dom@18\u002Fumd\u002Freact-dom.production.min.js\"",[112,213,140],{"class":118},[112,215,123],{"class":122},[112,217,145],{"class":118},[17,219,220,221,224,225,228,229,232],{},"But there's something to watch out for: the CDN order can't have ",[54,222,223],{},"react-dom.js"," first and ",[54,226,227],{},"react.js"," second. If you do that, you'll get an ",[54,230,231],{},"Uncaught TypeError: React is undefined React"," error.",[17,234,235],{},"To save you from tripping over setup mistakes, I've also prepped a CodePen environment so you can fork it and start practicing:",[28,237,238],{},[31,239,240],{},[78,241,244],{"href":242,"rel":243},"https:\u002F\u002Fcodepen.io\u002Fhsiangfeng\u002Fpen\u002FYzavBqZ",[82],"React CodePen starter environment",[246,247,255],"iframe",{"height":248,"style":249,"scrolling":250,"title":251,"src":252,"frameBorder":250,"loading":253,"allowTransparency":254,"allowFullScreen":254},300,"width: 100%;","no","(4)React Hook init","https:\u002F\u002Fcodepen.io\u002Fhsiangfeng\u002Fembed\u002FYzavBqZ?default-tab=html%2Cresult","lazy","true","\n  See the Pen \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fcodepen.io\u002Fhsiangfeng\u002Fpen\u002FYzavBqZ\">\n  (4)React Hook init\u003C\u002Fa> by Ray (\u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fcodepen.io\u002Fhsiangfeng\">@hsiangfeng\u003C\u002Fa>)\n  on \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fcodepen.io\">CodePen\u003C\u002Fa>.\n",[17,257,258,259,264],{},"If you haven't used CodePen before, you can check out my post \"",[78,260,263],{"href":261,"rel":262},"https:\u002F\u002Fisraynotarray.com\u002Fother\u002F20201020\u002F1425713503\u002F",[82],"A Ten-Minute Quick Start to CodePen"," (article in Mandarin)\" to get a quick feel for it, because a lot of the upcoming examples are going to live directly on CodePen.",[17,266,267,268,270,271,274,275,277,278,281,282,285,286,288,289,291,292,297],{},"Now, in those ",[54,269,123],{}," tags there's a ",[54,272,273],{},"crossorigin"," attribute. The ",[54,276,273],{}," setting basically tells the browser where the URL is coming from, and not to send any client info along. Its default value is ",[54,279,280],{},"anonymous",", so whether you write ",[54,283,284],{},"crossorigin=\"anonymous\""," or just ",[54,287,273],{},", you get the same thing. This isn't really the focus of this post though, I'm just mentioning it in passing. If you want to understand ",[54,290,273],{}," better, your best bet is to read the detailed explanation over on ",[78,293,296],{"href":294,"rel":295},"https:\u002F\u002Fdeveloper.mozilla.org\u002Fen-US\u002Fdocs\u002FWeb\u002FHTML\u002FAttributes\u002Fcrossorigin",[82],"MDN",".",[17,299,300],{},"Alright, let's get our first React environment ready!",[12,302,304],{"id":303},"hello-react","Hello React",[17,306,307,308,312],{},"Quick reminder again: I'd recommend clicking the ",[78,309,311],{"href":242,"rel":310},[82],"CodePen"," environment I shared above, because it already has the React CDN and JavaScript settings loaded in. To avoid version mismatches and environment issues, I strongly suggest forking it into your own CodePen to practice.",[17,314,315],{},"First we need to set up a basic piece of HTML:",[103,317,319],{"className":105,"code":318,"language":107,"meta":108,"style":108},"\u003Cdiv id=\"app\">\u003C\u002Fdiv>\n",[54,320,321],{"__ignoreMap":108},[112,322,323,325,328,331,333,336,338,340],{"class":114,"line":115},[112,324,119],{"class":118},[112,326,327],{"class":122},"div",[112,329,330],{"class":126}," id",[112,332,133],{"class":118},[112,334,335],{"class":136},"\"app\"",[112,337,140],{"class":118},[112,339,327],{"class":122},[112,341,145],{"class":118},[17,343,344],{},"You can think of this as a container. Its job is mainly to let React know where to inject its stuff, so the concept is very much like a container.",[17,346,347,348,351,352,355],{},"Next is the JavaScript part. We'll start by using ",[54,349,350],{},"document.querySelector('#app');"," to select the HTML we just created. If you'd rather use ",[54,353,354],{},"document.getElementById('app');",", that's totally fine too. Both give you the same result:",[103,357,361],{"className":358,"code":359,"language":360,"meta":108,"style":108},"language-js shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","const app = document.querySelector('#app');\n","js",[54,362,363],{"__ignoreMap":108},[112,364,365,369,372,375,378,382,385,388],{"class":114,"line":115},[112,366,368],{"class":367},"sWyjQ","const",[112,370,371],{"class":126}," app",[112,373,374],{"class":367}," =",[112,376,377],{"class":118}," document.",[112,379,381],{"class":380},"sj_SG","querySelector",[112,383,384],{"class":118},"(",[112,386,387],{"class":136},"'#app'",[112,389,390],{"class":118},");\n",[17,392,393,394,297],{},"So far we're still just writing plain JavaScript and haven't used any React syntax yet. So the first piece of React syntax we'll use is ",[54,395,396],{},"ReactDOM",[17,398,399,401,402,405,406,408,409,412],{},[54,400,396],{}," comes from the react-dom.development.js (or react-dom.production.min.js) CDN. It's basically React's DOM generator, and we'll use its ",[54,403,404],{},"createRoot"," method. ",[54,407,404],{}," takes the ",[54,410,411],{},"document.querySelector('#app')"," we just selected, and with that, React knows where to put things:",[103,414,416],{"className":358,"code":415,"language":360,"meta":108,"style":108},"const app = document.querySelector('#app');\nReactDOM.createRoot(app);\n",[54,417,418,436],{"__ignoreMap":108},[112,419,420,422,424,426,428,430,432,434],{"class":114,"line":115},[112,421,368],{"class":367},[112,423,371],{"class":126},[112,425,374],{"class":367},[112,427,377],{"class":118},[112,429,381],{"class":380},[112,431,384],{"class":118},[112,433,387],{"class":136},[112,435,390],{"class":118},[112,437,438,441,443],{"class":114,"line":148},[112,439,440],{"class":118},"ReactDOM.",[112,442,404],{"class":380},[112,444,445],{"class":118},"(app);\n",[17,447,448],{},"At this point there's basically nothing on the screen, since we haven't actually written anything yet. We're just doing the prep work.",[17,450,451,452,454,455,458,459,462,463,465],{},"Next we want to write the DOM we're going to render, and that rendering happens through ",[54,453,396],{},"'s ",[54,456,457],{},"render()"," function. So we'll need to save ",[54,460,461],{},"ReactDOM.createRoot(app);"," into a variable so we can call ",[54,464,457],{}," on it later:",[103,467,469],{"className":358,"code":468,"language":360,"meta":108,"style":108},"const app = document.querySelector('#app');\nconst root = ReactDOM.createRoot(app);\n",[54,470,471,489],{"__ignoreMap":108},[112,472,473,475,477,479,481,483,485,487],{"class":114,"line":115},[112,474,368],{"class":367},[112,476,371],{"class":126},[112,478,374],{"class":367},[112,480,377],{"class":118},[112,482,381],{"class":380},[112,484,384],{"class":118},[112,486,387],{"class":136},[112,488,390],{"class":118},[112,490,491,493,496,498,501,503],{"class":114,"line":148},[112,492,368],{"class":367},[112,494,495],{"class":126}," root",[112,497,374],{"class":367},[112,499,500],{"class":118}," ReactDOM.",[112,502,404],{"class":380},[112,504,445],{"class":118},[17,506,507,508,510],{},"So... how do we use ",[54,509,457],{},"? Easy, just write the HTML straight into it!",[103,512,514],{"className":358,"code":513,"language":360,"meta":108,"style":108},"const app = document.querySelector('#app');\nconst root = ReactDOM.createRoot(app);\n\nroot.render(\u003Ch1>Hello React\u003C\u002Fh1>);\n",[54,515,516,534,548,555],{"__ignoreMap":108},[112,517,518,520,522,524,526,528,530,532],{"class":114,"line":115},[112,519,368],{"class":367},[112,521,371],{"class":126},[112,523,374],{"class":367},[112,525,377],{"class":118},[112,527,381],{"class":380},[112,529,384],{"class":118},[112,531,387],{"class":136},[112,533,390],{"class":118},[112,535,536,538,540,542,544,546],{"class":114,"line":148},[112,537,368],{"class":367},[112,539,495],{"class":126},[112,541,374],{"class":367},[112,543,500],{"class":118},[112,545,404],{"class":380},[112,547,445],{"class":118},[112,549,551],{"class":114,"line":550},3,[112,552,554],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":553},true,"\n",[112,556,558,561,564,567,570,573,575],{"class":114,"line":557},4,[112,559,560],{"class":118},"root.",[112,562,563],{"class":380},"render",[112,565,566],{"class":118},"(\u003C",[112,568,569],{"class":122},"h1",[112,571,572],{"class":118},">Hello React\u003C\u002F",[112,574,569],{"class":122},[112,576,577],{"class":118},">);\n",[17,579,580,581,584,585,587],{},"That ",[54,582,583],{},"\u003Ch1>Hello React\u003C\u002Fh1>"," inside ",[54,586,457],{}," looks like HTML, but it's actually called JSX. It's a way of writing HTML inside JavaScript, and the name stands for JavaScript XML (an extension of JavaScript). We'll dig into JSX more in a later chapter.",[246,589,592],{"height":248,"style":249,"scrolling":250,"title":590,"src":591,"frameBorder":250,"loading":253,"allowTransparency":254,"allowFullScreen":254},"(5)React Example Default Project","https:\u002F\u002Fcodepen.io\u002Fhsiangfeng\u002Fembed\u002FmdxKoNd?default-tab=html%2Cresult","\n  See the Pen \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fcodepen.io\u002Fhsiangfeng\u002Fpen\u002FmdxKoNd\">\n  (5)React Example Default Project\u003C\u002Fa> by Ray (\u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fcodepen.io\u002Fhsiangfeng\">@hsiangfeng\u003C\u002Fa>)\n  on \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fcodepen.io\">CodePen\u003C\u002Fa>.\n",[17,594,595],{},"Congrats, you've built your first React! Pretty simple, right? If you want the above to be a bit more concise, you can write it like this:",[103,597,599],{"className":358,"code":598,"language":360,"meta":108,"style":108},"ReactDOM.render(\n  \u003Ch1>Hello React\u003C\u002Fh1>,\n  document.querySelector('#app')\n);\n",[54,600,601,610,624,638],{"__ignoreMap":108},[112,602,603,605,607],{"class":114,"line":115},[112,604,440],{"class":118},[112,606,563],{"class":380},[112,608,609],{"class":118},"(\n",[112,611,612,615,617,619,62